[vc_row overlay_dotted="" css=".vc_custom_1544097089058{padding-top: 9% !important;padding-bottom: 9% !important;}"][vc_column][havnor_section_title title_text="Hire Model FAQ" content_text="The art and science of asking questions is the source of all knowledge came a bubbling crude to the east side to a deluxe in the sky." btm_space="5%"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-two" one_active="true" active_tab="1"][vc_accordion_tab title="I am a CTO and I would like to handle the team by my own. Is it" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540528198267{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]For sure. With “Hire a team” model, you will have a direct access of a development team. “Pick your team, assign the tasks, discuss the sprint”; everything is possible. This business model is most advisable for CTO/ technical people and enterprise level firms who wants the constant changes in the system.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Are you open to do a test task to check your skill set?" sub_title="Sub Title 2"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540528220220{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Yes, with a minimal development charge; you can test our skills before making a final move. Please note that for such tasks, we work with 100% upfront payment only.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What steps I should follow to Hire a developer / team?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1542805610836{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]First of all - you should gather all the task for the developer which you want them to do for you. Based on the chosen developer and technology, finalize the agreement with sales team. Upon your confirmation, we will setup everything, and connect you &amp; developer.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How do I communicate &amp; give instructions to my hired developer?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540528273236{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]You can communicate the developers via Skype or any other instant message. You can share the task or instructions by using Instant Messenger, Email, phone etc. whichever suitable to you.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Are my business secrets and information safe with your company?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540528294259{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]Yes - The information shared by client for development purpose is property of the client. Neither the company nor appointed developer could sell, transfer or use the work product to any party other than the client.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What if the developer is long sick leave or leaves the company?"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1540528334155{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;}"]No problem. We can assign the alternate developer, if developer is sick or on long holidays. If any developer wants to leave the company then we have 3 months notice period time, in that time we manage to transfer the knowledge base to another developer, and non of our client’s work get suffered.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]
CONTENT;
